schedule.code.description: Generic decription of the code specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

schedule.code.output_flag.description: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used. {dynamic}

schedule.code.parameters.description: List of the code specific parameters in XML format {constant}

schedule.ids_properties.description: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

schedule.ids_properties.comment.description: Any comment describing the content of this IDS {constant}

schedule.ids_properties.homogeneous_time.description: 1 if the time of this IDS is homogeneous. In this case, the time values for this IDS are stored in ../time just below the root of this IDS. Otherwise, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. {constant}

schedule.waveform[:].description: Reference waveform to be used to drive feedback or feedforward controllers, or to control the controller switching itself

schedule.waveform[:].value.description: Values of the reference for the timebase

schedule.waveform[:].value.data.description: Values of the reference for the timebase {dynamic} [mixed]

schedule.waveform[:].value.data_error_in.description: Index in the error_description list for "data" {constant}
